org.hibernate.type.descriptor.java.spi

Interface ManagedJavaDescriptor<J>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    JavaTypeDescriptor<J>, Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    EmbeddableJavaDescriptor<T>, EntityJavaDescriptor<T>, IdentifiableJavaDescriptor<J>, MappedSuperclassJavaDescriptor<J>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractIdentifiableJavaDescriptor, AbstractManagedJavaDescriptor

    public interface ManagedJavaDescriptor<J>
extends JavaTypeDescriptor<J>
    Contract for "managed types", which is taken from the JPA term for commonality between entity, embeddable and "mapped superclass" types.

    • Method Detail

      • getSuperType

        ManagedJavaDescriptor<? super J> getSuperType()
        Obtain the super-type for this type.

        Note that for embeddables this is currently no-op, so at the moment really only IdentifiableType implementations can have a super-type. But Hibernate does have plans to add support for embeddable inheritance, so this is here for future compatibility.

        Returns:
        The type's super-type
